description:
Wuthering Heights is a classic novel by Emily Brontë, first published in 1847 under the pseudonym Ellis Bell. Set in the bleak Yorkshire moors, the story follows the tumultuous and passionate relationship between Catherine Earnshaw and the foundling Heathcliff.
The novel opens with Mr. Lockwood, a wealthy tenant, renting a house on the moors. He visits his landlord, Heathcliff, at the remote Wuthering Heights estate, where he learns the history of the Earnshaw family and their connection to Heathcliff. Through flashbacks, the story unfolds, revealing the tragic love between Catherine and Heathcliff, and the consequences that haunt the next generation.
